properties.headline: Lakeshore Flood Advisory issued January 8 at 7:00PM CST until January 9 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Milwaukee/Sullivan has issued a
Lakeshore Flood Advisory for lakeshore areas of Sheboygan and
Ozaukee counties...which is in effect from 3 AM to noon CST Thursday.

* Winds...Southeast winds will increase to 20 to 30 mph with a few gusts
to 35 mph late tonight and Thursday morning.

* Waves...Building to 9 to 11 feet.

* Impacts...Due to the high Lake Michigan water levels, pockets of
flooding of beaches and roads is possible near the lakeshore.
The high waves may cause bluff erosion along Lake Michigan.
properties.instruction:
A Lakeshore Flood Advisory indicates that onshore winds may
generate flooding of low areas along the lakeshore.

NWSheadline: LAKESHORE FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO NOON CST THURSDAY
